To subtract two numbers in base 3, we perform the arithmetic operations column by column, carrying over as needed:

\[
\begin{array}{}
& & 1 & 2 & 0 & 0 & 2 & 2 & 1 & 2 & 2 & 2_{3} \\
- & & 1 & 1 & 2 & 1 & 2 & 0 & 0 & 1 & 1 & 0_{3} \\
\hline
& & 0 & 0 & 0 & 2 & 0 & 2 & 2 & 1 & 1 & 2_{3} \\
\end{array}
\]

Therefore, \(1200221222_{3}-1121200110_{3} = 0002022112_{3}\).